HEADWORD: friars-cowls
<hw>friar's-cowls</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tuberous perennial (<spn>Arisarum
vulgare</spn>) having a cowl-shaped maroon or violet-black spathe; --
found in the Mediterranean, Canaries, and Azores.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> friars' cowl, <spn>Arisarum vulgare</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Friary</ent>⟦br⟧
